<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Lee_Byung-hun" title="Lee Byung-hun">Lee Byung-hun</a> as <a href="/wiki/Choi_Myung-kil" class="mw-redirect" title="Choi Myung-kil">Choi Myung-kil</a></li></ul>
A leader of one of the two ideological cliques that battles in the fortress trying to decide whether to make peace or fight against the <a href="/wiki/Qing_dynasty" title="Qing dynasty">Qing dynasty</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-10" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-10">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-11" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-11">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>


<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Kim_Yoon-seok" title="Kim Yoon-seok">Kim Yoon-seok</a> as Kim Sang-hun<sup id="cite_ref-12" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-12">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>
The other leader of the ideological clique who battles with Choi's opinion and firmly believes in defending the nation's dignity by fighting against the <a href="/wiki/Qing_dynasty" title="Qing dynasty">Qing dynasty</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-13" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-13">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>


<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Park_Hae-il" title="Park Hae-il">Park Hae-il</a> as <a href="/wiki/Injo_of_Joseon" title="Injo of Joseon">King Injo</a></li></ul>
The king who is in agony in the tense conflicts between his men over the fate of the nation.<sup id="cite_ref-14" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-14">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> 


<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Go_Soo" title="Go Soo">Go Soo</a> as Seo Nal-soi</li></ul>
A blacksmith sent out with a king's letter to recruit loyal forces. 


<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Park_Hee-soon" title="Park Hee-soon">Park Hee-soon</a> as Lee Shi-baek</li></ul>
The chief of the <a href="/wiki/Joseon" title="Joseon">Joseon</a> military who silently defends the mountain fortress in the extreme cold weather conditions.


